<br>
    It like a game of Hockey when your on the ice it a fierce competition for the win but once the game is over then we are all the same , players who play a game to have fun .   Some of us won and some of us lost , enjoy the game that you played because it not the last and next time the outcome may be different .<br>
<br>
I played in the Pre-Kunark times , back then it was easy to get to 50 and the number of high-end encounter was pretty slime ... you had Nagafen , Lady Vox , Plane of Fear and later Plane of Hate .  So you had 5-6 guilds that were fighting for 4 uber mob that respawned in a week and 2 planes to get armor from .   You can believe me that races for uber mob these days are pretty tame compared to back then.    And every guild was pretty even matched because gear was pretty much the same for everyone.  <br>
<br>
But i respect also those who reserve and announce intention to raid a zone .   Sometime you need to plan and prepare for these .  But i found ludicrous those who reserve spawns that have dynamic spawn time and are easily affected by server/zones ups and downs .   Half the challenge of these mobs is figuring out when they spawn and being ready for them when they do .<br>
<br>
This is not the opinion of my guild and there are probably alot in it that would disagree but this is how i played the game in the last 2 years and even with the tightest calendar system (we had one on the Rathe) we didnt reserve mobs that had varying spawn times.<br>
