<br>
Basically, CC/PO/Agony/FU(?)/Blight don't care about Event Announcements because they don't *have* to.  All they care about is what the other higher-end guilds have killed since the last patch so they can go kill what's left.  Event Anouncements is, however, a nice place to let other people know your intentions, and give a heads-up for other folks that may want to raid with you.  That's it's purpose now, and for that, it seems to work nicely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubraindrop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braindrop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/21/02 2:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=335.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Some people like the race. We had a great time racing EA for a Zlandi kill the other night. Both guilds even wiped <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Can't be more fun than that.<br>
